##"No discussion of the epidemic, no unauthorized interviews, " the official said

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

##Zhang Weilong, reporter, thepaper.cn

On February 18, a notice from Xiantao's health commission sparked heated debate, banning discussion of the outbreak in groups and giving interviews without permission.

Liu Wei, editor, video source, editor in charge: Zhou Kuanwei

The Xiantao Health Commission said in response to thepaper.cn Monday night that the announcement was true. Related personnel introduced that due to the fact that individual personnel of the city's health and sanitation system leaked personal information of confirmed patients and disseminated unconfirmed information about the epidemic during the pre-epidemic prevention work, to patients and their families and the city's epidemic prevention and control work has a certain impact. The notice was issued by Xiantao's Health Commission on the evening of February 18 to tighten work discipline and strictly regulate the channels through which documents are sent and information is released.

In response to netizens' discussion, the staff member said that the original intention of issuing the notice was not to block information about the outbreak or to refuse media interviews, but "there is something wrong with the relevant wording. ".

The Xiantao Health Commission's "notice on re-enforcing discipline during epidemic prevention and control" has attracted public attention. Image courtesy of the web

At present, the Xiantao Health Commission has held an emergency meeting on the same day, requesting the cadres and workers of the city's health care system to effectively improve their working methods, examine the existing problems and deficiencies, and adopt a more rigorous attitude and a more pragmatic style, do A good job in epidemic prevention and control.
